# Run Tests After Changes

After completing code changes (new features, bug fixes, refactors), run the relevant test suites to verify nothing is broken.

## Commands

- **Web app** (`apps/web`): `npx jest --no-coverage`
- **Server** (`apps/server`): `npx jest --no-coverage`
- **Targeted run** (faster): `npx jest path/to/file.test.ts --no-coverage`

## Conventions

- Web tests use `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` (Jest + jsdom)
- Server tests use `*.spec.ts` (Jest + node)
- Shared test factories live in `apps/web/src/test/factories.ts`
- Server mocks live in `apps/server/src/__mocks__/` (prisma.mock.ts, redis.mock.ts)

## When to Run

- After editing any `.ts` / `.tsx` source file in `apps/web/src/` or `apps/server/src/`
- After adding or modifying test files
- Before committing: run the full suite for the affected app
- Do NOT redirect test output to files (e.g. `2>err.txt`) — it creates untracked artifacts
